---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Beta" description="Run one chat UI for AI CLIs across your own devices.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Developer Control Plane</div>
      <h1>One chat interface for the AI tools running on your machines.</h1>
      <p>
        BridgeAIChat gives you a WhatsApp-style UI for CLI-native agents and models running on your own laptop,
        desktop, VPS, or Raspberry Pi. It connects over Tailscale, keeps device context visible, and avoids hosted AI gateways.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="button primary" href="/downloads">Get the beta</a>
        <a class="button" href="/docs/quickstart">Read the quickstart</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>What ships in beta</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Gateway-hosted web UI</li>
        <li>Standalone bridge-agent binaries</li>
        <li>Codex-first testing path</li>
        <li>Claude support with local quota/auth caveats</li>
        <li>GitHub Releases for all downloads</li>
      </ul>
      <pre>BridgeAIChat UI
  → Gateway
    → Tailscale
      → bridge-agent
        → local AI CLI</pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section grid three">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Own the runtime</h2>
      <p>No hosted model control plane. Devices run their own CLIs, tools, and context.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Multi-device by design</h2>
      <p>Each machine becomes a thread, so your laptop, VPS, and Pi stay visible and separate.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Beta-first distribution</h2>
      <p>Start from GitHub Releases, test on your own fleet, and iterate before package-manager polish.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
